(Security Change Log) Tj
0 -12 Td
(-------------------) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Recent operator security changes, sanitized for public sharing:) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- 2026-05-07: Restored Monad runtime settings with systemd drop-ins instead of editing vendor ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(unit files.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Why: Keeps the node configuration easier to audit and preserve across package updates while ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(restoring the known-good event-ring, RPC websocket, and CPU-placement behavior from the earlier) Tj
0 -12 Td
( install.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Privacy note: No command lines, passwords, keys, peer addresses, node identities, wallet-like) Tj
0 -12 Td
( values, or public IP addresses are recorded here.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- 2026-05-07: Restricted Monad secret-bearing files to owner-only read/write permissions.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Why: The local keystore environment file and node identity key files were more broadly ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(readable than necessary. Owner-only permissions reduce local accidental disclosure risk without) Tj
0 -12 Td
( changing node behavior.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Privacy note: File paths are summarized by purpose; key contents and unlock values are never ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(included.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- 2026-05-07: Confirmed normal local users cannot read the Monad BFT process command line or ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(environment through procfs.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Why: The BFT binary currently accepts its keystore unlock value through a command-line ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(option, so process-argument visibility matters. Existing procfs hiding reduces exposure to non-) Tj
0 -12 Td
(privileged local users.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Privacy note: The actual process command line and keystore unlock value are intentionally ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(omitted.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- 2026-05-07: Documented the remaining upstream security limitation for Monad BFT keystore ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(unlock handling.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Why: A cleaner design would let operators pass the keystore unlock value through a protected ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(file, stdin, systemd credential, or similar non-argv mechanism. The current local binary help ) Tj
0 -12 Td
(only exposes a command-line unlock option.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  Privacy note: This notes the design limitation only; no secret [redacted] is recorded.) Tj
ET
